The model quality (based on MCC) was higher for all datasets except for one, which performed poorly. Models derived from all datasets were statistically significant with MCC and G-mean values >0.7. The significance of the dataset was also verified by the high F–score values (>0.8), while sensitivity and specificity parameters were >0.75 for most models. The F–score is calculated through the following equation: 1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
